Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.

If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.7f109100-bacd-4ec2-940e-37c467b90618.transition.description=Unable to read children from directory. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.a8f1ef75-1b94-488c-a196-6596a3430c58.transition.description=${current}'s children were added. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.c3983e3e-4cc8-473d-8e5a-a0ba3d7a0372.transition.description=children were ${children} 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.dd40d5e1-6192-4786-b71e-21f7b7e4dd9c.transition.description=processing ${current}. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.description=
This flow demonstrates how to traverse a directory tree.

Inputs\:
    source - The directory to get the children of.
    delimiter - A delimiter to put in between each child of this directory.
Default value\: , (comma).
    username - The username to traverse directories as.
    password - The password for username.

Responses\:
    success - The sample completed successfully. Directory was traversed without error.
    failure - The sample failed. Possible causes are\: unable to login to host, bad directory name, filesystem error.

Note\:
    The flow will go through every sub folder of the source. If you set source to a folder with many children (such as c\:\ on a windows system) then it will take this flow a long time to complete.

Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.e53918b5-940f-4c70-8c0e-324f89ec0048.transition.description=${current} is a directory. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.e95724b3-cb4c-48ce-8cd8-afa0f04ec0ea.description=
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The path to check.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success - The operation succeeded.
49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.e9bfc32b-04bb-4d41-b245-d81d4a7d9b6e.transition.description=${current} is a file. 49786e2d-8cf5-4aed-b098-53b8f7219771.ea49b2a8-b119-4f8b-896e-9240453d967c.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
